title: Social Emotional Development
subject: Preschool Early Learning and Development Standards (2024-)

document.title: Preschool - Maine's Early Learning and Development Standards

49AA2BE5E4D74E69834B1D37756AE024.description:
Begins to think about a
situation from the point of
view of others.

0ADC4F86094641549B50A54A085EB1A5.description:
Notices that other children
might communicate
differently. (e.g., through
nonverbal communication,
different languages and/or
dialects).

C0B054438D6F4FFC8A65BA1431748ADF.description:
Recognizes and discusses
similarities and differences in
others.

F946854374FA4CE486DB9D3AF7D15B9F.description:
Develops relationships with
others based upon shared
experiences.

316DA4DDDAB74CA0B08842F44E058DA1.description:
Notices similarities and
differences in others.

4E997D844C9D4C558FE3C1F55BD5D3BF.description:
Uses play to explore, practice,
and understand social roles.

06FBC184F33B44F6B08B76D4CDC53DA8.description:
Knows and expresses self as
a part of diverse groups. (e.g.,
family, preschool class, faith
community, etc.).

64BBFAEB5AEA487098516411D6CCA086.description:
Helps self and others when
needed.

15B3AB7483BD467DBE5682FD16A7CFD9.description:
Communicates wants and
needs in a group setting.

BE2F85C0DAF24838B5F3D577681E9A07.description:
Notices who is absent from a
group setting.

5CBDFFD91151448794F0132B77ED184B.description:
Shows or communicates care
or concern for others.

4E5A7D259BD044AF8676CA686722AF05.description:
Shows an increased ability to
be friendly and flexible in play
and to work cooperatively to
resolve conflicts with peers.

9A143009ADE44769AD8C7831C38FD89F.description:
Uses different turn-taking
strategies (e.g., trading,
setting a timer, etc.).

41B65CDE35B844C7ADBD7C3CF6E2D9AF.description:
Works cooperatively with
others to plan, create, and
organize activities during play
and solve problems as they
arise.

AD6283D8B6C640CFA3828770EEDD6E61.description:
Shares information with at
least one trusted person.

2E120EAD4FE943A8AE1EB26688DC2278.description:
Seeks help when needed for
emotional support.

69EDE57C6C604ED0B29F7951A2A66A43.description:
Asks questions and checks
with an adult as needed while
exploring their environment.

9A69F9E32A7045518EF10C5FCCB152D0.description:
Leads or participates in
cooperative play with others

3EA57543BDCF4905B40FE1EC5690FF25.description: Engages in interactive play with others.

72657C4E69AA4656975F38DA8DD530B7.description:
Engages in parallel play (i.e.,
plays next to or near others
without trying to influence
the play or behavior of
others).

DF5D2C2F410F4C0C829C60DB5008FD58.description:
Identifies known safety roles
and distinguishes between
trusted and unknown adults.

442AF01789714D24B7E6892DF7A48EDA.description:
Follows guidance for
behavior in different
environments.

FEBA4C852A47429CADA4500F9BA142AF.description:
Approaches others for
assistance when needed.

5D09BCA2502042D9BAD5664C0CBDF93B.description:
Separates from adults
in familiar settings, with
assistance.

6222DD9A635A4BCB8FC71625234194E4.description: Social Development: a child’s ability to create and sustain meaningful relationships with adults and other children.

434937615F274E4AACA163FB5AF20FB2.description:
Follows rules in new or
diverse settings.

4066BF45FEB5472692B88236C836F962.description:
Anticipates, with assistance,
what will be needed in
diverse settings.

FC5FF1537A16495987075283F82875E4.description:
Given prior notice (e.g., with
a visual schedule or verbal/
nonverbal adult cues),
adjusts to changes from one
activity/setting to the next.

6317D38229EF434B913CE3DAA7C56109.description:
Demonstrates ability to be
flexible and adjust to routine
or unexpected changes,
including physical setting,
daily schedule, staffing and
group size/attendance, with
adult support.

72B04D851D48455CAC75AFD5AE001BDB.description:
Begins to demonstrate
ability to be flexible or adjust
to routine or unexpected
changes including physical
setting, daily schedule,
staffing and group size/
attendance.

ED8F1DCACBAF491C8B41CD13B27229BA.description:
Explores objects and
materials and interacts with
others in a variety of new
settings.

ACD475DE3C7044A9B99920A23CD4F0A4.description:
Shows progress in expressing
feelings, needs, and opinions,
in difficult situations such as
conflicts, without harming
self, others, or property.

BBFE2C52DA014A2DA3062A24F6445BB0.description:
Asks “what” and “why”
questions to understand the
effects of behavior.

D6DAAD6B5106488C996474CC0BBB5B00.description:
Labels emotions of self and
others, with support.

A3A3E0B954E44D4F8F4175D846AE68DD.description:
Demonstrates empathy
through comfort and care of
others. (e.g., asking “Are you
okay?” or giving/requesting a
hug or high-five).

A5A9FFF5690F4A1E933E78CA03906FE7.description:
Demonstrates ability to be
kind to self and others in a
variety of situations.

B5F57A572CBF4370BDF73CBFEE5EBB3C.description:
Demonstrates a beginning
ability to identify basic
feelings of self and others in
a variety of situations.(e.g.,
identifying that self or others
feels happy, sad, or angry).

CCDA8E25E87A467A9610A9C213915EE9.description:
Shows beginning ability to
co-regulate emotions and
behaviors with a trusted,
regulated adult.

D88EAAAE1A3046CB9ED21FA6C1E07DFD.description:
Demonstrates understanding
of cause and effect of own
actions.

29B43B36D6F74E558391C4A4E92F51F6.description:
Waits for their turn in simple
game or use of equipment.

7A1CF6AA018F441D8157A9C07A03BFBF.description: Shows progress in sharing materials with others.

8099212769CB4B1B9F86DE3AC3409689.description:
With support, demonstrates
the ability to follow
developmentally appropriate
rules and routines.

CB47F76B5037491E9F5E8624C173CDD6.description:
With support, demonstrates
an understanding of
developmentally appropriate
rules and routines.

4EC0654466AD428B826E439EB39BA579.description:
With support, listens to
instructions before beginning
an activity.

34D67ED669484425A5E7018B2923827C.description:
Seeks adult support and
engages in finding solutions
to resolve conflict with peers.

8562C6A7DAC04E34916016324FBD7A68.description:
Expresses wants, thoughts,
needs, and feelings
through various methods of
communication.

C67822FF15184942B640C02BEE649BF3.description:
Develops listening skills with
intentional adult instruction
and support.(e.g., teaching
children that listening can
look like giving their attention
to others or events in various
ways).

751CED713FB3444798CACC9773D7F412.description:
Begins to notice the cause
and effect of own actions.

B147C41577A344EBA0F7292F42D9B761.description:
With adult guidance, uses
materials and equipment
purposefully and safely.

F557009F7F0E47F39E0B2AD946019731.description:
Shows progress in sharing the
attention of a trusted adult
caregiver.

027F28D8A0BA4103837841B8DE6800F6.description:
Shows progress in ability to
recognize and communicate
feelings and emotions.

B196F2FD667A4AAD8CA91C706266671E.description:
Shows progress in the
ability to express and
identify feelings, needs, and
opinions across learning
environments.

2D350D6119B94A79963494C3764BE8EF.description:
Demonstrates understanding
of and ability to communicate
developmentally appropriate
basic safety guidelines.

B1636E02DCF44C3484D88A09EA78449B.description:
Shows ability to respect
personal space and
boundaries of other people.
(e.g., checking before
touching another person
or showing concern when
stepping on someone’s foot).

706AEBB9D4464A19B73FD2A13F72A225.description:
Shows ability to take care
of personal or shared
possessions. (e.g. backpack,
toys, books).

20A79141894B43EDB7F51BE8AD8CD720.description:
Uses a variety of materials
with curiosity and interest.

5F6E8BBBC8694E5090C8C343A1AD774D.description:
Initiates actions or activities
with peers. For example,
inviting a friend to play.

FB7FE6A83FA146DB921926A30BE2A71C.description:
Tries new things and
improves new skills with
practice.

1C85D6CED2DE46589B14667CB95D3B62.description:
Demonstrates self-direction
by making choices among
peers, activities, and
materials.

D5C4E12C3CAA4814B955CAABAE2ECB12.description:
Expresses and/or
demonstrates an awareness
of self as an individual
with certain wants, needs,
abilities, characteristics,
preferences, and rights.

5834966D494C4423BBBAB8825AA10662.description:
Begins to show awareness
of own autonomy and
boundaries.

3D3F8E2F7B1E47ACA4A6AB313B891915.description:
Expresses self in different
roles during pretend play.

A51648E92C544BC4BAA6CB4756012199.description:
Begins to see self as an
individual with their own
wants, needs, skills, and
abilities.

EEFE8879BEE64FFD827DBF1630225E7E.description: Emotional Development: understanding how and why feelings and emotions occur in self and others and developing effective ways for managing those feelings.
